desc: Hi! You can find more of my decks Here. This deck was made with subs2srs. If you use it with Morphman, the focus morph field is named "Morph" in this template. There are instructions on how to use the card style inside the card template. If you have any issue with this deck or another, reach me on reddit or Discord. If you want to know how much you can understand a anime or a video game based on your level, you can use links and tutorials from this spreadsheet. Go into the deck's Option - Description panel to delete this text.
name: The Garden of Words

tmpls.name: Sentence

fields: Until I entered high school two months ago,  didn't know...
The dampness of my uniform's hem, soaked by someone else's umbrella...
The smell of naphthalene, clinging to someone's suit...
The warm body pushed up against my back...
The chill breeze of the air conditioner against my face...
Thank you for riding with us.
When I was little the sky was closer... So much closer.
That's why I like the rain, as with it comes the smell of the sky.
And often, on rainy mornings, nstead of transferring to the subway, I exit out the station gates.
But, I think I've seen her somewhere...
If so, will you stay here with me?
This morning, the JMA has declared the start of the rainy season in Kyushu, 5 days earlier than average.
Nagasaki, Saga, Kumamoto, and Kagoshima prefectures
expect strong rains over a wide area.
Great. Dinner will be ready soon.
Lucky us, we get all the croquettes to ourselves.
She left a letter saying not to go looking for her.
I'm sure she'll be back after fighting with her boyfriend.
I've picked out a place. 'll be leaving next month.
Don't you think that's why mom ran out?
I wish she could just let her children go, you know?
She's the one who's making the rounds dating younger men, damn it.
Oh, yeah? Well then, I'm gonna go live with my boyfriend!
She's got those youthful looks, after all.
That's 'cause she's never worked hard her entire life.
You're the one who's been piling on the years.
You do the dishes. I've aged enough.
Won't you be glad to have more space?
Hey, have you heard of this?
Ask Ma when she gets back.
On sunny mornings, I transfer to the subway and head here, like I'm supposed to.
But I think to myself "This is not what I should be doing now."
And your office... Is it closed today?
And drinking beer in the park in the morning.
Drinking beer alone isn't good for your health.
You need to eat something with it.
You know a lot for a high school kid.
It's not me. My mom's the drinker.
You just thought to yourself "This woman's a freak," didn't you?
It's okay. We're human, after all. We've all got our little quirks.
Okay, it's about time for me to go.
I've decided to only skip school on rainy mornings.
Then, maybe we'll see each other again.
It was the first day of Kanto's rainy season.
I know it seems out of touch, but I enjoy creating designs and making shoes.
Of course, I'm still terrible at it.
But despite it all,  want to make it my career... if I can.
I've never told this to anyone before.
Do you have any idea how late you are?
You know why I've called you here, right?
Evenings, before I went to sleep...
Mornings, from the moment I woke up...
I realized I was praying for rain.
I realized that on sunny days,  was in a terrible, childish place.
She exists in a world of working adults, so very far away from me...
To me she represents nothing less than the very secrets of the world.
Honestly, there are only two things  know for sure.
One: she must think of me as just some 15 year old kid.
And two: making shoes is the only thing that will lead me out of this place.
For your safety, please stay  behind the yellow line.
Please be careful of the closing doors.
I thought you might not come today.
It's a miracle you haven't been fired yet.
Wow! Is that a shoe design?
Come on, sit down over there.
I'm going to eat breakfast. Would you like to join me?
Thank you, but I've brought my own.
What? I cook sometimes, you know.
Wait, I'm not really that good a...
That's a side of you I didn't expect.
Sorry. But it's tasty in its own way.
Thank you. What could the three of you have gotten me?
Hey... Do you think it's too late for me?
And you know what?  could actually taste the food.
So your taste disorder has improved?
But just a little while ago, all I could taste was alcohol and chocolate.
I think you deciding to just quit was really for the best.
You speak to me so gently, like you're touching something fragile.
But back then, when I found it hard even to breathe, you didn't believe me. You only listened to the voices around you.
Then we'll start the paperwork for you leaving after the holiday. I'll notify the higher-ups.
Okay. Sorry to cause you all this trouble even after we split up.
About that old woman you met.
You know, the one you keep talking about who brings her lunch box to the park.
It seems like you've really struck a chord.
It's raining again today in Kanto.
Here at Shinjuku Station's south exit, the commuters all have umbrellas in their hands.
I always end up eating your food, see...
And you said you wanted it, right?
I'm actually making a pair of shoes right now.
I haven't decided whose shoes yet... They're women's shoes.
But, I haven't been able to get them right, and...
You know... Before I knew it, I wasn't able to walk properly anymore.
Are you talking about your job?
Yeah... About a lot of things.
I don't know anything about her.
Her job, her age... What worries she carries... Even her name...
And yet I can't help but be charmed by her.
The rainy season is officially over 10 days later than normal in the Kanto region.
The current temperature in the city s 26 degrees.
Like someone just flicked a switch, the sunny days came one after another.
Oh sure, now I think to myself "I'm glad that he's not skipping class anymore"...
...I wish the rainy season had never ended.
I can't believe we're in Shinjuku.
These are the Japanese gardens, right? Where should we go next?
Isn't there a greenhouse? Let's check it out.
It's like a totally different place on sunny days.
Hey, why don't you eat dinner with us, Takao?
Sorry, but I've got my part-time job today.
And I don't want to impose.
The opposite! I'm going to be living with him from now on, so just this once...
He's got a bright future, doesn't he? I wonder if he'd make shoes for me?
Who knows? Teenagers' interests change on a whim...
My brother moved out, and the rainless days continued.
I had no excuse to head to that place. And then, it was summer vacation.
I worked part-time almost every day over the summer.
Hmm, maybe chicken with cashew nuts?
I wanted to earn what I could for tuition to a vocational school.
Tools and leather cost money, too.
I think it's clinging to those feelings that is keeping me a little kid.
That's why I've decided to create shoes that'll make her want to get up and walk.
What~ will the weather~ be tomorrow~?
I'm not even a bit smarter at the age of 27 than I was at the age of 15.
I've always been here, stuck in the same place.
to have got that confused for a week!
English class is no big deal.
Hey, long time no see. Looks like you guys got a tan.
Yeah, we went to the beach a bunch.
You're still as pale as ever. What'd you do over summer break?
Worked the whole time. The whole time?
That's a lonely way to spend your high school days.
School, part-time job, housework. School, part-time job, housework.
Now that you mention it, you are late a lot, Akizuki.
Yup, this guy never shows up for 1st period when it rains.
I've got a condition where I can't ride the subway on rainy mornings.
Sato, save it for later. Miss Yukino!
Same goes for the rest of you.
I'll be here until after 5th period. After that, I'd be happy to.
You didn't hear about Yukino quittin'?
No. I didn't even know who she is.
You have old man Takehara for lit, right?
Yukino was always having trouble with the 3rd year girls.
Yeah, but Miss Yukino didn't do anything wrong.
Someone's boyfriend fell for Miss Yukino, and as payback everyone in the class treated Miss Yukino terribly.
They spread so many rumors even her parents heard about them.
It went so far she couldn't come to school any more.
Yukino's just too kind. She should have brought it right to the police.
We told Mr. Itou again and again!
But he didn't want to make trouble for the school in public.
But man, you sure go through 'em.
It seems like Miss Yukino is quitting.
Like I care about what happens to that slutty hag.
Who does this guy think he is?
Who are you? Fallen for that old hag?
What a creep! Does he even know how old she is?
Poor guy, she must have tricked him.
She might go for him now, though.
Since she ain't a teacher no more.
A faint clap of thunder Even if rain comes not
I will stay here Together with you
That's the right response to the tanka  told you when we first met.
If it rains, I wonder if you will be staying here?
In response to that verse, I answer...
Even if it doesn't rain, I will be here.
It was in the classic Japanese literature textbook.
I thought you would realize  was a classic literature teacher.
I mean, everyone at school knows about me.
But you're always off in your own little world, aren't you?
Hey, what happened to your face?
I was acting like you and drank too much beer.
Then I tripped and fell on the Yamanote line platform.
Just kidding. I got in a fight, that's all.
Look... It looks like we just swam across the river.
I think I've fallen in love with you.
I'm going to be moving next week. Back to my hometown in Shikoku.
I made the decision a while back.
I was practicing how to walk on my own, there in that place. Even if I'm barefoot...
So I want to thank you for everything, Akizuki.
Um, thank you for lending me these clothes.
I made this lunch for myself, but I made too much. So if you'd like...
I haven't decided whose shoes yet...
I was acting like you and drank too much beer
Then I tripped and fell on the Yamanote line platform.
I will stay here Together with you
Yukino, please forget what I said earlier.
I was wrong... I hate you after all.
Ever since we first met, you struck me...
Drinking beer in the morning, spouting off some random tanka at me...
You listen all day to other people talking, yet never say a peep about yourself...
You knew I was a student, didn't you?
If I'd known you were a teacher,  would have never told you about the shoes.
After all, you think 'll never amount to anything!
So why didn't you say anything to me?
You thought maybe you'd humor the little kid's fantasies for a while?
Tell me I'll never live up to my expectations! Tell me I'll never measure up to my dreams!
You knew from the very beginning!
So tell me, god damn it!
Tell me I'm in your way! Tell me that little kids should run along to school!
Tell me that you hate me!
It's because you act like that!
You never say what's important! You pretend it's none of your business!
You've been living your whole life alone!!
Every morning I put on my suit to go to school...
But I was... scared... I just couldn't go...
Summer ended, and the time came to switch to our winter uniforms...
I got terrible marks on my final exams...
I wasted who knows how many pieces of expensive leather...
I worked part-time over winter break as well...
And every time I added a layer to my clothing, I wondered to myself... "how is she doing?"
I was practicing how to walk, too.  believe that now.
One day, when I can walk much farther on my own...
